.SH "NAME"
mc_close \- close a Mc connection
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
\fBvoid mc_close(mc_t *\fR\fB\fIctx\fR\fR\fB);\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
The \fImc_close()\fR function shall close the connection established with the backend set in the context\&.
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
.sp
There is no return value\&.
.SH "EXAMPLE"
.sp
.if n \{\
.RS 4
.\}
.nf
mc_t *ctx;

ctx = mc_new_tcp("127\&.0\&.0\&.1", 502);
if (mc_connect(ctx) == \-1) {
    fprintf(stderr, "Connection failed: %s\en", mc_strerror(errno));
    mc_free(ctx);
    return \-1;
}

mc_close(ctx);
mc_free(ctx);
.fi
